    "We briefly present the reasons for selecting the datasets.",
    "Open-Domain Dialogue (ODD) Differently from other datasets, DailyDialog dialogues only involve two participants (Tiedemann, 2009; Baumgartner et al., 2020), are not audio transcriptions (Godfrey et al., 1992), have more than two exchanges between the participants (Rashkin et al., 2019), and are not restricted by a persona (i.e.",
    "few sentences describing the user's interests) (Zhang et al., 2018; Xu et al., 2022a).",
    "Knowledge-Grounded Dialogue (KGD) Wizard of Wikipedia provides a test set with an unseen set of documents (Zhou et al., 2018; Komeili et al., 2022) and its knowledge has not changed over time (i.e.",
    "comparable with previous/future studies) (Gopalakrishnan et al., 2019; Hedayatnia et al., 2020)."
  ],
